HEADWORD: Siesta
<hw>Si*es"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., probably
fr. L. <ets>sessitare</ets> to sit much or long, v. freq. of
<ets>sedere</ets>, <ets>sessum</ets>, to sit. See <er>Sit</er>.]</ety>
<def>A short sleep taken about the middle of the day, or after dinner; a
midday nap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sieur</ent>⟦br⟧
